<seg id=1> Overhead Railway Project Will Start Again In Bangkok </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> (FNA news from Bangkok) Thailand Ministry of Communications declared yesterday that Thailand would require the HK stock company Hopewell Group who undertook the project of Bangkok overhead railway and highway system to pay a compensation of US$6800 million(approximately 11 billion Singapore dollars) for not fulfilling the contract on time. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> Thailand Vice Minister of Communications Palardie said that Thailand ministry of Communications and State Department of Railway had the right of recourse to Hopewell Group of US$6800 million in compensation for finishing only 12% of the planned project in the last 8 years. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Since the end of Thailand economic crisis, the Hopewell Group has negotiated many times with relevant authorities in Thailand on its financial troubles and land requisition troubles aggravated by devaluation of Thai Bahts, but has reached no results. </seg>
<seg id=5> Thus, the Hopewell Group asked the Thailand government for a compensation of 100 billion Thai Bahts(4200 million Singapore dollars) for its capital invested and the already finished part of the project. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> The Thailand government said yesterday, they were planning to start again this US$3200 million worth of project but in a smaller scale, </seg>
<seg id=7> and they would never let the Hopewell Group take part in it. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> Palardie also revealed that the Germany government and Germany KFW were interested in recovery of this project and had decided to offer 100 million Thai Bahts for research on feasibility of overhead railway and highway in Bangkok. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> German Siemens Company is working together with a local Thailand company for the construction of another 23km long electronic railway in Bangkok. </seg>
</p>
